 As a human player, I would choose to play a strategy called Tit-for-Tat, which is a popular strategy in repeated games. In this strategy, I will start by choosing R on my first move, aiming to cooperate and get the highest possible payoff of 45$ (if the other player also chooses R).

After that, I will mimic their previous move for the next several rounds. If they continue to play fairly and choose R, we both will keep earning 45$ per round. However, if they choose B in any round, I will immediately switch my strategy and respond with B in all future rounds as well (since they are taking advantage of my cooperation).

For this game with 75 rounds, the optimal strategy would be to start with R and then adapt to the other player's moves. This approach maximizes our earnings while also punishing any unfair moves made by the opponent. I will choose: {R}
